-about-what-experts-say-effects-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etablets%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20our%20young%20toddlers%2C%20and%20we%20did%20not%20have%20any%20gaming%20consoles%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fignoring-traditional-parenting-advice-screen-time-veggies-less-anxious-parent-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPads%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20our%20children%20as%20they%20grew%20older.%20But%20we%20quickly%20realized%20that%20with%20middle%20school%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20there%20was%20the%20social%20assumption%20that%20our%20child%20will%20have%20her%20own%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recall%20my%20daughter%20being%20in%20her%20last%20year%20of%20elementary%20school%20(fifth%20grade%20where%20we%20are)%20and%20telling%20me%20that%20all%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20kids%20in%20her%20class%20had%20phones%20and%20brought%20them%20to%20school.%20Now%2C%20I'm%20sure%20not%20all%20of%20them%20did%2C%20but%20she%20certainly%20felt%20like%20she%20was%20in%20the%20minority%20by%20not%20having%20one.%20Turns%20out%2C%20she%20was%20right.%20From%20watching%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcell-phone-for-kids-youtube-parenting-regret-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%20videos%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20bus%20to%20school%20to%20sharing%20selfies%20and%20browsing%20TikTok%2C%20many%20of%20her%20classmates%20were%20already%20equipped%20with%20their%20own%20phones%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteens-dont-have-social-media-accounts-not-allowed-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20in%20elementary%20school!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220842d9e5-c451-4807-91a3-95fd1205ad27%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20timing%20wasn't%20right%20for%20us%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20always%20told%20our%20daughter%20that%20she'd%20get%20a%20phone%20when%20she%20was%20older.%20We%20didn't%20know%20if%20it%20would%20be%20when%20she%20was%20in%20middle%20school%20or%20when%20she%20was%20a%20teenager%2C%20we%20just%20knew%20it%20would%20be%20sometime%20later.%20It%20felt%20way%20too%20early%20for%20her%20to%20have%20access%20to%20the%20world%20in%20her%20pocket.%20Plus%2C%20who%20was%20she%20going%20to%20call%20or%20text%20anyway%3F%20She%20saw%20her%20friends%20at%20school%20or%20sports%20practice%20every%20day%20and%20was%20often%20able%20to%20play%20in%20the%20neighborhood%20with%20her%20buddies.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20of%20course%2C%20was%20met%20with%20some%20frustration%20initially%2C%20but%20she%20understood%20our%20stance%20as%20parents%20and%20didn't%20seem%20to%20mind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-childhood-phone-use-health-social-effects-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20having%20her%20own%20phone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20honestly.%20We%20coordinated%20her%20time%20with%20friends%20as%20we%20always%20had%2C%20since%20those%20very%20first%20preschool%20playdates%20with%20other%20moms%20and%20her%20classmates.%20I%20took%20care%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20some%20point%20along%20the%20way%2C%20while%20she%20was%20still%20in%20elementary%20school%2C%20I%20learned%20about%20the%20%26quot%3BWait%20Until%208th%26quot%3B%20pledge%20and%20how%20it%20encourages%20parents%20to%20wait%20to%20get%20their%20kids%20a%20smartphone%20until%20the%20end%20of%20eighth%20grade.%20Initially%2C%20this%20sounded%20like%20an%20amazing%20idea%20to%20both%20my%20husband%20and%20me.%20By%20following%20this%20pledge%2C%20we%20would%20preserve%20our%20daughter's%20childhood%20through%20middle%20school%20and%20would%20delay%20the%20inevitable%20issues%20that%20will%20come%20with%20her%20having%20access%20to%20much-older%20content%20via%20a%20smartphone.%20We%20pledged%20to%20each%20other%20that%20this%20was%20our%20plan.%20Little%20did%20we%20know%20that%20we'd%20be%20some%20of%20the%20only%20parents%20in%20our%20social%20group%20doing%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fe4b29cc-6f69-46c1-8e96-aa913d319b71%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThings%20started%20to%20change%20in%20middle%20school%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20middle%20school%20started%2C%20we%20asked%20around%20to%20see%20which%20kids%20had%20phones%20and%20which%20didn't.%20It%20seemed%20that%20nearly%20three%20out%20of%20four%20kids%20did.%20Our%20decision%20really%20wasn't%20influenced%20by%20those%20results%3B%20rather%2C%20we%20made%20our%20decision%20based%20on%20personal%20values%20and%20research%20we%20had%20done%20around%20children%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaughter-entering-high-school-with-dumb-phone-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccess%20to%20phones%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20social%20media.%20Sixth%20and%20seventh%20grade%20went%20by%2C%20and%20we%20found%20it%20was%20manageable%20to%20communicate%20with%20our%20daughter%20when%20we%20needed%20to%2C%20she'd%20often%20ask%20another%20parent%20to%20text%20us%20or%20call%20from%20a%20phone%20in%20her%20school's%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%2C%20however%2C%20was%20how%20I%20was%20stuck%20coordinating%20all%20her%20social%20plans%2C%20and%20often%20with%20her%20own%20friends!%20The%20majority%20of%20her%20friends'%20parents%20stopped%20being%20as%20involved%20with%20social%20planning%20because%20they%20had%20gotten%20their%20kids%20phones%2C%20and%20they%20were%20now%20managing%20it%20on%20their%20own.%20My%20daughter%20not%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkid-wants-smartphone-not-ready-decision-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efelt%20left%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20planning%2C%20she%20was%20sometimes%20left%20out%20all%20together%20when%20she%20wasn't%20invited%20to%20group%20gatherings%20because%20her%20friends%20didn't%20have%20direct%20access%20to%20her.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20often%20felt%20irritated%20and%20annoyed%20trying%20to%20get%20a%20hold%20of%20parents%20who%20used%20to%20do%20the%20planning%20with%20me.%20They%20had%20cut%20out%20the%20middleman%20and%20moved%20on%20to%20a%20different%20social%20landscape%20without%20us.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20frustration%20seemed%20to%20outweigh%20the%20negatives%20of%20having%20a%20phone%20in%20our%20eyes%2C%20so%20we%20thought%20long%20and%20hard%20and%20decided%20to%20reevaluate%20our%20stance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2259d2f5b1-2490-4695-8cb5-854e5845c81f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%208th%20grade%2C%20we%20reevaluated%20our%20needs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFast-forward%20to%20the%20summer%20before%20eighth%20grade%2C%20and%20we%20realized%20that%20our%20daughter%20really%20did%20need%20a%20phone.%20Not%20for%20social%20media%2C%20mindless%20scrolling%2C%20or%20binge-watching%20shows%2C%20but%20just%20to%20be%20able%20to%20take%20her%20own%20photos%20and%20communicate%20with%20us%20and%20with%20her%20friends%20on%20her%20own%20terms%20(with%20parental%20guidance%20in%20place).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20surprised%20her%20with%20a%20phone%20this%20past%20fall%20and%20she%20has%20been%20extremely%20grateful%2C%20responsible%2C%20and%20mindful%20about%20its%20usage.%20She%20texts%20and%20FaceTimes%20her%20friends%2C%20takes%20a%20ton%20of%20photos%2C%20has%20an%20app%20that%20tells%20her%20when%20to%20water%20her%20plants%2C%20and%20sometimes%20sneaks%20in%20an%20episode%20or%20two%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Office%26quot%3B%20before%20bed.%20She%20does%20not%20have%20any%20social%20media%20apps%20and%20we%20do%20not%20plan%20to%20allow%20her%20to%20have%20any%20until%20she%20is%2016%2C%20she's%2014%20now.%20I'm%20curious%20to%20see%20if%20we%20make%20it%20to%20eighth%20grade%20with%20our%20younger%20child%2C%20or%20if%20we%20will%20shift%20perspectives%20on%20access%20to%20technology%20with%20this%20ever-changing%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-without-cell-phone-left-out-of-group-plans-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740218701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b5fe62eb4be2fff9a4fe46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-without-cell-phone-left-out-of-group-plans-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20waited%20longer%20than%20other%20parents%20to%20get%20our%20teen%20a%20phone.%20I%20got%20stuck%20being%20her%20social%20coordinator%20and%20she%20missed%20out%20on%20invites%20to%20group%20events.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Laurie%20Syphard)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-without-cell-phone-left-out-of-group-plans-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20renowned%20market%20strategist%20who%20called%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%20warns%20US%20stocks%20are%20at%20'serious%20risk'%20as%20tech%20analyst%20optimism%20starts%20to%20sour%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22new%20york%20stock%20exchange%20trader%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F535989506bb3f75d24347316%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221869%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20trader%20reacts%20after%20the%20closing%20bell%20of%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange%20on%20November%205%2C%202008.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FLucas%20Jackson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAlbert%20Edwards%20warns%20declining%20analyst%20optimism%20for%20US%20tech%20stocks%20could%20mean%20trouble.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHistorically%2C%20souring%20analyst%20optimism%20has%20led%20to%20poor%20stock-market%20performance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETech-stock%20capitalization%20now%20exceeds%20dot-com%20bubble%20levels%2C%20leaving%20the%20market%20vulnerable%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESociete%20Generale%20strategist%20Albert%20Edwards%20has%20long%20been%20skeptical%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-bubble-sp500-ai-soft-landing-edwards-socgen-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20stocks%20in%20the%20US%20could%20live%20up%20to%20the%20hype%3C%2Fa%3E%20surrounding%20them.%20Now%2C%20it%20looks%20like%20stock%20analysts%20covering%20the%20tech%20sector%20are%20starting%20to%20grow%20dubious%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20client%20note%20published%20Thursday%2C%20the%20often-bearish%20Edwards%20published%20a%20series%20of%20charts%20that%20he%20thinks%20should%20give%20investors%20pause%20as%20stocks%20remain%20close%20to%20all-time%20highs.%20They%20show%20analyst%20optimism%20souring%20on%20tech%20stocks%2C%20which%20have%20underpinned%20the%20market's%20impressive%20rally%20%E2%80%94%20a%20development%20he%20said%20puts%20stocks%20%26quot%3Bat%20serious%20risk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20a%20few%20of%20them.%20First%20is%20the%2012-month%20moving%20average%20of%20the%20percentage%20of%20analysts%20who%20are%20upgrading%20earnings-per-share%20forecasts.%20It's%20fallen%20from%20around%2058%25%20to%2050%25%20since%20the%20start%20of%202024%2C%20yet%20the%20Nasdaq%20100%20has%20continued%20its%20surge.%20Historically%2C%20downtrends%20like%20this%20in%20optimism%20have%20coincided%20with%20a%20dip%20below%20the%20Nasdaq's%20200-day%20moving%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20rapid%20decline%20in%20analyst%20optimism%20for%20the%20Nasdaq%20100%20is%20anything%20to%20go%20by%2C%20the%20tide%20is%20going%20out%20fast%2C%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIndeed%2C%20it%20is%20a%20minor%20macro%20miracle%20that%20the%20index%20is%20still%20trading%20above%20its%20200%20mav%20let%20alone%20record%20highs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221972%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22tech%20analyst%20optimism%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b90061c832c3638fa4f107%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22888%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESociete%20Generale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20been%20a%20disconnect%20between%20analysts'%20expectations%20for%20earnings%20and%20how%20well%20earnings%20have%20fared%2C%20with%20reality%20lagging.%20Now%2C%20it%20looks%20like%20expectations%20are%20starting%20to%20turn%20south%20as%20trailing%20earnings%20flatten%20and%20fall%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221922%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22trailing%20and%20forward%20eps%20estimates%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b90112c040bd1b4ca2dea9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22924%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESociete%20Generale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20estimates%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20Composite%201500%20have%20started%20to%20turn%20downward%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20their%20ChatGPT-driven%20rebound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20chart%20below%20that%20investors%20should%20be%20really%20nervous%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BNotwithstanding%20the%20'blips'%20from%20games%20played%20around%20reporting%20rounds%2C%20analyst%20optimism%20for%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20been%20a%20series%20of%20lower%20highs%20and%20lower%20lows.%20Both%20the%206%20and%2012%20month%20moving%20averages%20are%20now%20turning%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221914%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22profit%20estimates%20s%26amp%3Bp%20composite%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b900dc4e7cbbbe3dc440fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22932%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESociete%20Generale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20Edwards%20emphasizes%2C%20the%20problem%20with%20souring%20expectations%20is%20that%20investors'%20outlook%20is%20already%20at%20exuberant%20extremes%2C%20and%20anything%20that%20falls%20short%20of%20those%20extremes%20is%20a%20downside%20miss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20ordinary%20times%20this%20would%20not%20be%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20equity%20investors%2C%20but%20it%20is%20potentially%20a%20big%20risk%20when%20we%20are%20at%20nose-bleed-high%20valuations%20and%20optimism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20look%20at%20how%20frothy%20the%20tech%20sector%20and%20US%20stocks%20have%20gotten.%20Tech%20stocks%20now%20make%20up%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20the%20market%20than%20during%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%20%E2%80%94%20which%20Edwards%20is%20famous%20for%20calling%20%E2%80%94%20and%20US%20stocks%20are%20now%20an%20exorbitant%2075%25%20of%20global%20market%20cap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221928%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22us%20tech%20sector%20market%20cap%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b90096c832c3638fa4f10c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESociete%20Generale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20actual%20market%20performance%20tends%20to%20trend%20with%20where%20analyst%20estimates%20go.%20A%20worsening%20outlook%20suggests%20the%20rally%20could%20start%20to%20slow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221952%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22analyst%20optimism%20and%20stock%20performance%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b902d6c832c3638fa4f152%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22926%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESociete%20Generale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20US%20analyst%20optimism%20is%20turning%20downward%20might%20this%20be%20enough%20to%20pull%20the%20rug%20from%20under%20what%20many%20see%20as%20an%20extremely%20expensive%20equity%20market%2C%20flirting%20with%20all-time%20highs%3F%26quot%3B%20Edwards%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20stocks%20have%20faced%20a%20few%20hurdles%20in%20recent%20weeks%20that%20