%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20wildfires%2C%20for%20example%2C%20it's%20relatively%20straightforward%20for%20an%20insurance%20company%20to%20predict%20a%20home's%20risk%20by%20assessing%20the%20amount%20of%20brush%20near%20the%20house%20or%20its%20proximity%20to%20a%20high-risk%20hillside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hail%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5b6966c3bda1c723008b4568%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELarge%20hailstones%20in%20Colorado%20in%202018.%3Cp%3EAP%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHail%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20is%20more%20of%20a%20mystery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsurance%20companies%20can't%20predict%20exactly%20where%20severe%20hail%20storms%20will%20fall%20or%20how%20big%20the%20stones%20might%20be.%20That%20uncertainty%2C%20combined%20with%20the%20escalating%20cost%20of%20payouts%20for%20previous%20hail%20storms%2C%20has%20made%20some%20companies%20raise%20homeowners'%20premiums.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20really%20understand%20why%20or%20how%20to%20fix%20it%2C%20and%20so%20uncertainty%20makes%20it%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20McClure%20said%20of%20insurers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20premiums%20rise%2C%20coverage%20is%20shrinking%2C%20putting%20a%20squeeze%20on%20many%20homeowners.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-insurers-protect-properties-wildfires-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsurance%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20entire%20replacement%20of%20a%20roof%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20old%20it%20was.%20Now%2C%20it's%20more%20common%20for%20them%20to%20only%20cover%20the%20cash%20value%20of%20the%20roof%20or%20limit%20their%20coverage%20based%20on%20the%20roof's%20age%2C%20McClure%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20homeowners%20in%20these%20areas%20should%20be%20scrutinizing%20their%20plans%20more%20than%20ever.%20%26quot%3BMake%20sure%20they%20understand%20how%20their%20roof%20is%20covered%2C%26quot%3B%20McClure%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221ac363e6-1ba9-455a-9d05-12691f21a90e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EClimate%20change%20is%20likely%20to%20make%20hailstones%20bigger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%20isn't%20helping%20the%20matter%20because%20it%20creates%20bigger%20hailstones%2C%20said%20Victor%20Gensini%2C%20an%20environmental%20professor%20at%20Northern%20Illinois%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHail%20forms%20when%20warm%20air%20on%20the%20ground%20during%20a%20storm%20creates%20an%20updraft%2C%20which%20pushes%20raindrops%20towards%20colder%20parts%20of%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20freezing%20them%2C%20and%20creating%20hailstones.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-50-home-runs-mlb-games-season-study-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWarmer%20air%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20therefore%2C%20leads%20to%20bigger%20stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20warm%2C%20humid%20air%20basically%20serves%20as%20gasoline%2C%26quot%3B%20Gensini%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20storms%20in%20Alabama%2C%20Colorado%2C%20and%20Texas%20set%20new%20records%20for%20the%20largest%20hailstones%20in%20each%20state's%20history%2C%20all%20over%204%20inches.%20A%20study%20Gensini%20and%20his%20colleagues%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dba05fd45d35f62271a2902a711823891252d01436cbea8a2620b61d3b9ac5eb9%26postID%3D67927be722e74339bb4bbc38%26postSlug%3Dhail-stone-storm-damage-threat-to-american-homes-insurance-premiums-2025-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41612-024-00728-9%2523%253A~%253Atext%253DNear%25252Dsurface%252520hailstones%252520%25253C4%252520cm%252Care%252520expected%252520across%252520the%252520U.S.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20predicted%20a%2015%25%20to%2075%25%20increase%20in%20l