carrying%20five%20experimental%20payloads.%20After%20a%20record-breaking%20908%20days%20in%20space%2C%20the%20X-37B%20completed%20its%20mission%20and%20landed%20at%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20in%20November%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20much%20of%20the%20X-37B%20program%20is%20classified%2C%20the%20secrecy%20fueled%20speculation%20about%20the%20purpose%20of%20its%20mission%20sets%2C%20with%20some%20speculating%20that%20the%20space%20plane%20could%20be%20a%20weapons%20platform%20or%20used%20for%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20from%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELaunched%20from%20a%20SpaceX%20rocket%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20front%20view%20of%20the%20nose%20of%20the%20X-37B%20following%20its%20landing%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8b7f9c832c3638fa4e3b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20front%20view%20of%20the%20nose%20of%20the%20X-37B%20following%20its%20landing%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20courtesy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20X-37B%20embarked%20on%20its%20seventh%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-launch-space-force-secretive-plane-x-37b-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20mission%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20December%202023%2C%20launching%20from%20the%20Falcon%20Heavy%20rocket%2C%20manufactured%20and%20launched%20by%20Elon%20Musk's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-launched-a-top-secret-military-spaceplane-into-orbit-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-launched-a-top-secret-military-spaceplane-into-orbit-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFalcon%20Heavy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20capable%20of%20launching%20payloads%20over%2022%2C000%20feet%20above%20Earth%2C%20so%20the%20X-37B%20was%20launched%20higher%20than%20any%20other%20spaceplane%20and%20flew%20in%20a%20highly%20elliptical%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20purpose%20of%20its%20seventh%20mission%20was%20to%20experiment%20with%20%26quot%3Bfuture%20space%20domain%20awareness%20technologies%26quot%3B%20and%20analyze%20the%20radiation%20effects%20on%20plant%20seeds%20during%20spaceflight%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Space%20Force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20key%20objective%20of%20the%20X-37B's%20current%20mission%20is%20to%20refine%20and%20execute%20novel%20maneuvers%20called%20aerobraking%2C%20using%20the%20drag%20of%20Earth's%20atmosphere%20to%20quickly%20shift%20into%20low%20orbit%20and%20safely%20dispose%20of%20service%20module%20components%20using%20minimal%20fuel.%20Changing%20orbit%20is%20a%20crucial%20capability%20should%20the%20spaceplane%20be%20used%20to%20upgrade%20US%20satellites%20or%20disable%20those%20of%20its%20adversaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EShrouded%20in%20secrecy%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Personnel%20wearing%20protective%20gear%20surrounded%20the%20X-37B%20after%20it%20landed%20on%20the%20runway%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8b7f9c040bd1b4ca2d15e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPersonnel%20wearing%20protective%20gear%20surrounded%20the%20X-37B%20after%20it%20landed%20on%20the%20runway%20at%20NASA's%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20courtesy%20photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20image%20taken%20by%20its%20onboard%20camera%20shows%20just%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20the%20X-37B%2C%20few%20photos%20of%20the%20vehicle%20itself%20are%20available%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20video%20montage%20posted%20on%20X%20in%202023%20included%20a%20blink-and-you'